-- Legal & General Pretax Profit Falls; Dividend is Increased
-- B y   K e i t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 2012-03-14T07:09:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/legal-general-pretax-profit-falls-dividend-is-increased.html
Legal & General Group Plc (LGEN) , the
fourth-biggest U.K. insurer by market value, said full-year
pretax profit fell 12 percent to 956 million pounds.  The insurer also raised its dividend 35 percent to 6.4
pence per share.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Keith Campbell at 
 k.campbell@bloomberg.net  